Vincent.

52:19.762 --> 52:21.831
Vincent, wake up.

52:33.976 --> 52:36.778
<i>Now that we can have more
complicated conversations...</i>

52:36.978 --> 52:39.048
<i>the smart people at NASA
have sent me instructions</i>

52:39.248 --> 52:40.783
<i>on how to hack the Rover...</i>

52:40.983 --> 52:43.051
<i>so that it can talk to</i> Pathfinder.

52:43.251 --> 52:45.220
<i>If I hack a tiny bit of code...</i>

52:45.420 --> 52:48.457
<i>just 20 instructions in the
Rover's operating system...</i>

52:48.657 --> 52:49.993
<i>NASA can link the Rover to</i> Pathfinder's

52:50.193 --> 52:51.993
<i>broadcasting frequency...</i>

52:52.193 --> 52:54.997
<i>and we're in business.</i>

53:07.777 --> 53:09.044
"Mark...

53:09.244 --> 53:11.881
"this is Vincent Kapoor.

53:12.081 --> 53:15.452
"We've been watching you since Sol 54.

53:16.318 --> 53:19.021
<i>"The whole world is rooting for you.</i>

53:19.655 --> 53:22.959
<i>"Amazing job getting</i> Pathfinder.

53:23.159 --> 53:25.562
<i>"We're working on rescue plans.</i>

53:25.762 --> 53:28.798
<i>"Meantime, we're putting
together a supply mission...</i>

53:28.998 --> 53:33.903
"to keep you fed until <i>Ares 4</i> arrives."

53:50.385 --> 53:51.921
Okay.

54:01.396 --> 54:02.865
Okay.

54:03.532 --> 54:05.768
"Glad to hear it. Really
looking forward to not dying."

54:17.979 --> 54:19.582
"How's the crew?"

54:19.782 --> 54:22.753
"What did they say when
they found out I was alive?"

54:43.405 --> 54:45.640
Guys, can we get some space please?

54:45.840 --> 54:46.709
Me?

54:46.909 --> 54:48.044
Yeah, you.

54:48.244 --> 54:50.046
Give me a sec.

54:55.985 --> 54:57.988
Just tell him.

55:06.461 --> 55:12.568
"We haven't told the
crew you are alive yet.

55:14.202 --> 55:18.575
"We need them to concentrate
on their mission."

55:30.887 --> 55:33.557
What the fuck?

55:34.023 --> 55:35.492
What the fuck?

55:42.532 --> 55:45.066
Okay, he says, "They don't know I'm alive?

55:45.266 --> 55:47.035
"What the..." F-word.

55:47.235 --> 55:48.403
F-word in gerund form.

55:48.603 --> 55:50.206
F-word, again, "is wrong with you?"

55:52.742 --> 55:56.145
"Mark, please watch your language.

55:56.345 --> 55:58.314
"Everything you type

55:58.514 --> 56:03.053
"is being broadcast
live all over the world."

56:05.086 --> 56:06.590
Yeah?

56:14.597 --> 56:15.764
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

56:18.501 --> 56:19.568
Yes, sir.

56:19.768 --> 56:22.071
He is under a tremendous amount of stress.

56:23.206 --> 56:24.767
I understand. We're working on it.

56:25.173 --> 56:26.841
I'm sure he didn't mean what he said.

56:27.041 --> 56:28.978
Thank you, Mr. President.

56:30.478 --> 56:31.647
Problem is, Mark's right.

56:31.847 --> 56:34.015
The longer we wait, the
worse it's gonna get.

56:34.215 --> 56:35.584
We need to tell the crew.

56:35.784 --> 56:38.252
You're bringing this up while
Vincent is in Pasadena...

56:38.452 --> 56:39.988
so he can't argue the other side.

56:40.188 --> 56:41.524
I shouldn't have to answer to Vincent.

56:41.724 --> 56:43.660
Or anyone else.

56:45.394 --> 56:47.430
It's time, Teddy.

57:11.119 --> 57:12.488
<i>Commander Lewis?</i>

57:12.688 --> 57:14.157
Go ahead.

57:14.722 --> 57:16.592
<i>Data dump is almost complete.</i>

57:17.425 --> 57:19.695
Copy that. On my way.

57:32.273 --> 57:33.575
You're in a hurry.

57:33.775 --> 57:35.078
Yeah.

57:35.278 --> 57:37.113
My son turned three yesterday.

57:37.313 --> 57:39.448
Should be pictures of the party.

57:49.624 --> 57:51.426
Got a batch of personals.

57:51.626 --> 57:54.164
Dispatching them to your laptops now.

57:55.097 --> 57:58.200
I don't need to read Vogel's
weird German fetish emails.

57:58.400 --> 58:00.202
They're telemetry updates.

58:00.402 --> 58:02.003
Hey, whatever does it for you, man.

58:03.072 --> 58:04.339
There's a video message.

58:04.539 --> 58:06.475
It's addressed to the whole crew.

58:06.675 --> 58:09.211
Play it. Come on, guys.

58:09.411 --> 58:11.079
I wanna get in on
that telemetry action.

58:14.983 --> 58:18.020
<i>Hi, hello. It's Mitch. Mitch Henderson.</i>

58:18.220 --> 58:20.189
<i>I have some news.</i>

58:20.389 --> 58:23.459
<i>There's no subtle way to put this.</i>

58:23.659 --> 58:25.528
<i>Mark Watney is still alive.</i>

58:25.728 --> 58:27.562
Oh, my God.

58:27.762 --> 58:29.798
<i>I know that's a surprise and I know</i>

58:29.998 --> 58:31.332
<i>you will have a lot of questions.</i>

58:31.532 --> 58:34.303
<i>But here are the basics.</i>

58:34.503 --> 58:37.340
<i>He's alive and he's healthy.</i>

58:38.807 --> 58:42.377
<i>We found out two months ago
and decided not to tell you.</i>

58:42.577 --> 58:43.845
- Two months?
- Oh, my God.

58:44.045 --> 58:46.682
<i>I was strongly
against that decision.</i>

58:46.882 --> 58:49.685
<i>We're telling you now because...</i>

58:49.885 --> 58:52.354
<i>we finally have
communication with him...</i>

58:52.554 --> 58:55.490
<i>and a viable rescue plan.</i>

58:55.690 --> 58:57.526
<i>We'll give you a write-up
of what happened,</i>

58:57.726 --> 58:59.093
<i>a full write-up of everything.</i>

58:59.293 --> 59:00.796
<i>But it's not your fault.</i>

59:00.996 --> 59:04.066
<i>Mark stresses that
every time it comes up.</i>

59:04.532 --> 59:07.503
<i>So... Yeah...</i>

59:09.170 --> 59:11.506
<i>Take some time to absorb this.</i>

59:11.706 --> 59:14.209
<i>And send all the questions you want.</i>

59:14.409 --> 59:16.312
<i>We'll answer them.</i>

59:17.313 --> 59:19.115
<i>All right. Henderson out.</i>

59:19.315 --> 59:21.417
Holy shit, he's alive.

59:22.016 --> 59:23.185
I left him behind.

59:23.385 --> 59:24.220
- No.
- No.

59:24.420 --> 59:26.055
We all left together.

59:26.255 --> 59:28.390
You were following orders.

59:31.527 --> 59:34.129
I left him behind.

59:43.572 --> 59:44.272
<i>So now that
NASA can talk to me,</i>

59:44.472 --> 59:46.075
<i>they won't shut up.</i>

59:46.275 --> 59:48.845
<i>They want constant updates
on every Hab system...</i>

59:49.045 --> 59:50.578
<i>and they got a room full of people</i>

59:50.778 --> 59:52.548
<i>trying to micromanage my crops.</i>

59:52.748 --> 59:54.684
<i>Which is awesome.</i>

59:55.383 --> 59:57.453
<i>Look, I don't mean to sound
arrogant or anything...</i>

59:57.653 --> 01:00:02.492
<i>but I am the greatest
botanist on this planet, so...</i>

01:00:03.492 --> 01:00:04.794
<i>One big bonus</i>

01:00:04.994 --> 01:00:06.796
<i>to this communication
with NASA again...</i>

01:00:06.996 --> 01:00:08.430
<i>is the email. I'm getting them again.</i>

01:00:08.630 --> 01:00:10.799
<i>Big data dumps like when
I was on the</i> Hermes.

01:00:10.999 --> 01:00:12.868
<i>I even got one from the president.</i>

01:00:13.068 --> 01:00:15.537
<i>The coolest one, though,
the coolest one I got...</i>

01:00:15.737 --> 01:00:16.772
<i>was from University of Chicago,</i>

01:00:16.972 --> 01:00:18.540
<i>my alma mater.</i>

01:00:18.740 --> 01:00:21.209
They say that once you
grow crops somewhere...

01:00:21.409 --> 01:00:23.612
you've officially colonized it.

01:00:24.112 --> 01:00:26.716
<i>So, technically...</i>

01:00:27.382 --> 01:00:29.284
<i>I colonized Mars.</i>

01:00:33.722 --> 01:00:36.192
In your face, Neil Armstrong.

01:00:36.791 --> 01:00:38.426
In other news, there's been a request...

01:00:38.626 --> 01:00:40.162
for me to pose for a photograph

01:00:40.362 --> 01:00:42.731
on my next transmission.

01:00:43.398 --> 01:00:44.499
I'm trying to figure out whether

01:00:44.699 --> 01:00:47.368
I should go with "High School Senior"...

01:00:47.568 --> 01:00:50.874
or "coquettish ingenue."

01:00:52.574 --> 01:00:53.776
But I'm not really sure

01:00:53.976 --> 01:00:55.897
how that's gonna look with my spacesuit on.

01:01:21.503 --> 01:01:23.239
Hey!

01:01:25.273 --> 01:01:26.841
What is he doing?

01:01:27.041 --> 01:01:29.111
I asked for a photo,
and what, he's The Fonz?

01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:30.912
<i>Just be grateful we got
you something, Annie.</i>

01:01:31.112 --> 01:01:33.082
I can't use this,
Vincent, and you know that.

01:01:33.282 --> 01:01:34.582
I need a picture of his face.

01:01:34.782 --> 01:01:36.318
<i>I could tell him to
take off his helmet...</i>

01:01:36.518 --> 01:01:38.086
but then he'd, you know, die, so...

01:01:39.688 --> 01:01:40.589
<i>We'll release the photo</i>

01:01:40.789 --> 01:01:41.890
<i>when we detail the rescue operation.</i>

01:01:42.090 --> 01:01:43.725
I want to announce we're launching

01:01:43.925 --> 01:01:45.026
some supplies to him next year...

01:01:45.226 --> 01:01:47.229
during the Hohmann Transfer Window.

01:01:47.429 --> 01:01:49.598
Bruce, your team's still on schedule?

01:01:49.798 --> 01:01:51.533
<i>It'll be tight, but we'll make it.</i>

01:01:51.733 --> 01:01:53.435
Nine-month travel time.

01:01:53.635 --> 01:01:55.903
That puts the probe to Mars on Sol 868.

01:01:56.103 --> 01:01:58.006
Did we get the botany team's analysis?

01:01:58.206 --> 01:02:01.511
<i>Yeah, they estimate Mark's
crops will last till Sol 912.</i>

01:02:01.711 --> 01:02:04.046
<i>They grudgingly admit that
he's doing great work.</i>

01:02:04.246 --> 01:02:05.379
Grudgingly?

01:02:05.579 --> 01:02:06.415
<i>Yeah. Mark has a tendency to tell them</i>

01:02:06.615 --> 01:02:07.649
<i>to have sex with themselves...</i>

01:02:07.849 --> 01:02:09.618
<i>whenever they question
one of his decisions.</i>

01:02:09.818 --> 01:02:10.720
Get him in line, Vincent.

01:02:10.920 --> 01:02:12.620
We can't afford any miscommunication.

01:02:12.820 --> 01:02:14.290
I hate this margin.

01:02:14.490 --> 01:02:18.394
912 Sols worth of food.
We get there on 868.

01:02:18.960 --> 01:02:21.698
And that's assuming nothing goes wrong.

